o II della Torre和Mattea della Torre的儿子，于大约1200年出生。他与da Niguarda结婚。他们至少是1个女儿的父母。他在意大利隆巴迪亞米蘭諾被列为iv signore di milano e capitano perpetuo del popolo。他去世于1265年9月24日享年66岁，埋葬在意大利隆巴迪亞米蘭諾米蘭諾亞拉瓦勒。"},"hr":{"um 1200–24 SEP 1265":"oko 1200.–24. rujna 1265.","1200–1265":"1200–1265","–1263":"–1263","–Male":"preminuo","–Female":"preminula","1220–Female":"1220–preminula","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1170–1214":"1170–1214","24 SEP 1265":"24. rujna 1265.","1214":"1214","um 1240":"oko 1240.","1200":"1200","1287":"1287","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","um 1200":"oko 1200.","1240":"1240","1170":"1170","post 1214":"1214.","Chiaravalle, Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italia":"Chiaravalle, Milano, Milano, Lombardia, Italija","Italy":"Italija"},"cs":{"um 1200–24 SEP 1265":"okolo 1200–24. září 1265","1200–1265":"1200–1265","–1263":"–1263","–Male":"Zesnulý","–Female":"Zesnulá","1220–Female":"1220–Zesnulá","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1170–1214":"1170–1214","24 SEP 1265":"24. září 1265","1214":"1214","um 1240":"okolo 1240","1200":"1200","1287":"1287","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","um 1200":"okolo 1200","1240":"1240","1170":"1170","post 1214":"1214","Chiaravalle, Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italia":"Chiaravalle, Milano, Milano, Lombardia, Itálie","Italy":"Itálie"},"da":{"um 1200–24 SEP 1265":"omkring 1200–24. september 1265","1200–1265":"1200–1265","–1263":"–1263","–Male":"Afdød","–Female":"Afdød","1220–Female":"1220–Afdød","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1170–1214":"1170–1214","24 SEP 1265":"24. september 1265","1214":"1214","um 1240":"omkring 1240","1200":"1200","1287":"1287","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","um 1200":"omkring 1200","1240":"1240","1170":"1170","post 1214":"1214","Chiaravalle, Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italia":"Chiaravalle, Milano, Milano, Lombardia, Italien","Italy":"Italien"},"nl":{"um 1200–24 SEP 1265":"circa 1200–24 september 1265","1200–1265":"1200–1265","–1263":"–1263","–Male":"Overleden","–Female":"Overleden","1220–Female":"1220–Overleden","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1170–1214":"1170–1214","24 SEP 1265":"24 september 1265","1214":"1214","um 1240":"circa 1240","1200":"1200","1287":"1287","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","um 1200":"circa 1200","1240":"1240","1170":"1170","post 1214":"1214","Chiaravalle, Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italia":"Chiaravalle, Milano, Milano, Lombardia, Italië","Italy":"Italië"},"en":{"um 1200–24 SEP 1265":"about 1200–24 September 1265","1200–1265":"1200–1265","–1263":"–1263","–Male":"Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","1220–Female":"1220–Deceased","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1170–1214":"1170–1214","24 SEP 1265":"24 September 1265","1214":"1214","um 1240":"about 1240","1200":"1200","1287":"1287","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","um 1200":"about 1200","1240":"1240","1170":"1170","post 1214":"1214","Chiaravalle, Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italia":"Chiaravalle, Milano, Milan, Lombardy, Italy","Italy":"Italy","nameMeanings":[{"name":"della","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Italian: habitational name from Pella in Novara province.","Italian: possibly a shortened form of <i>Iacopella</i>, a pet form of the personal name <i>Iacopa</i>, feminine form of <i>Iacopo</i> (see   Jacob  ), or of <i>Filippella</i>, a pet form of <i>Filippa</i>, feminine form of   Filippo  .","possibly Catalan: from old Catalan <i>pella</i> ‘used clothes’, perhaps a nickname for someone poorly dressed."],"variants":[{"name":"Jacob","meanings":["Jewish, English, Welsh, German, Portuguese, French (mainly Alsace and Lorraine), Walloon, Breton, Dutch, Flemish, Swedish, Danish, and Norwegian: derivative, via Latin <i>Jacob(us)</i>, from the Hebrew personal name <i>Ya‘aqob</i> (<i>Yaakov</i>). In the Bible, this is the name of the crafty younger twin brother of Esau (Genesis 25:26), who took advantage of the latter's hunger and impetuousness to persuade him to part with his birthright ‘for a mess of potage’. The name is traditionally interpreted as coming from Hebrew <i>akev</i> ‘heel’: Jacob is said to have been born holding on to Esau's heel. In English usage the name <i>Jacob</i> is regarded as distinct from the name   James  , but they are of identical origin. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed cognates from other languages, for example Assyrian/Chaldean or Arabic   Yaqub  ,   Yakub  ,   Yacoub  , or   Yacob  , Slovenian   Jakob   and <b>Jakop</b>, Czech and Slovak   Jakub  , and also their patronymics and other derivatives (see examples at   Jacobs   and   Jacobson  ). The name <i>Jacob</i> is also found among Christians in southern India (compare   Chacko  ), but since South Indians traditionally do not have hereditary surnames, the southern Indian name was in most cases registered as such only after immigration of its bearers to the US."]}]},{"name":"Torre","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Rocco, Angelo, Salvatore, Carmelo, Vito, Antonio, Carmine, Pietro, Sal, Sebastiano, Agostino, Bartolo.  Spanish Jose, Francisco, Carlos, Julio, Alvaro, Eduardo, Elvira, Ernesto, Fernando, Gregorio, Guillermo, Jorge.","Italian: topographic name for someone who lived near a tower, <i>torre</i> (from Latin <i>turris</i>), usually a defensive fortification or watchtower, or a habitational name from any of the places called with this word, as for example Torre Annunziata or Torre del Greco in Naples province, Torre de’ Passeri (Pescara, Abruzzo), or Torre di Ruggiero (Catanzaro, Calabria). Compare   La Torre  .","Galician, Catalan, Aragonese, Spanish, and Portuguese: topographic name from <i>torre</i> ‘(watch) tower’ (of the same etymology as 1), or a habitational name from any of numerous places called (La) Torre in Spain and Portugal. Compare Spanish   De la Torre   and   La Torre  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Torres","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Luis, Carlos, Manuel, Jesus, Francisco, Pedro, Miguel, Jorge, Raul, Rafael.  Portuguese Ligia, Anatolio, Catarina, Paulo, Albeiro, Gonsalo, Joaquim, Lidio, Omero, Wenceslao.","Galician, Catalan, Spanish, Portuguese, and Jewish (Sephardic): habitational name from any of numerous places called Torres, all named with the plural of <i>torre</i> ‘tower’ (see   Torre  ). As a Jewish name, it was often adopted at the moment of conversion to Roman Catholicism. After the return to Judaism (generations later), some descendants retained the name their families used as Catholics. Compare   De Torres  .","Italian: habitational name from Torres in Belluno or Porto Torres in Sassari. In southern Italy the surname is sometimes of Spanish origin (see 1 above)."]},{"name":"Torrisi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Angelo, Alfio, Carmelo, Giuseppe, Palma, Sal, Carmine, Domenic, Mauro, Salvator, Vito.","Italian: topographic name for someone living by a tower, from a variant of <i>torrese</i>, an adjectival derivative of   Torre  . The form is a hybrid of standard Italian <i>torese</i> and southern Italian <i>turrisi</i>."]},{"name":"La Torre","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Alberto, Carlos, Fernando, Jorge, Angel, Juan, Luis, Manuel, Ricardo, Roberto, Alvaro.  Italian Rocco, Vito, Angelo, Antonio, Salvatore, Carmelo, Cosimo, Dante, Eligio, Ferdinando, Lorenzo, Pasquale.","Spanish; Italian (mainly southern; also <b>Latorre</b>): habitational name from any of various places in Spain and Italy named La Torre or Torre, from <i>torre</i> ‘(watch) tower’ (see   Torre  ), with the definite article <i>la</i>. Compare Spanish   De la Torre   and Italian   Della Torre  ."]},{"name":"Torri","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Giovanni, Aldo, Carlo, Fiorella, Geno.","Italian: patronymic or plural form of   Torre  ."]}]},{"name":"Filippo","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Greek.  See  <b>Philip</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Philip","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Filippo della Torre was born about 1200 as the son of Giacomo II della Torre and Mattea della Torre. He married da Niguarda. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. His occupation is listed as iv signore di milano e capitano perpetuo del popolo in Milan, Lombardy, Italy. He died on 24 September 1265, at the age of 66, and was buried in Chiaravalle, Milano, Milan, Lombardy, Italy."},"et":{"um 1200–24 SEP 1265":"umbes 1200–24. september 1265","1200–1265":"1200–1265","–1263":"–1263","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1220–Female":"1220–Surnud","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1170–1214":"1170–1214","24 SEP 1265":"24. september 1265","1214":"1214","um 1240":"umbes 1240","1200":"1200","1287":"1287","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","um 1200":"umbes 1200","1240":"1240","1170":"1170","post 1214":"1214","Chiaravalle, Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italia":"Chiaravalle, Milano, Milano, Lombardia, Itaalia","Italy":"Itaalia"},"fi":{"um 1200–24 SEP 1265":"noin 1200–24. syyskuuta 1265","1200–1265":"1200–1265","–1263":"–1263","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1220–Female":"1220–Kuollut","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1170–1214":"1170–1214","24 SEP 1265":"24. syyskuuta 1265","1214":"1214","um 1240":"noin 1240","1200":"1200","1287":"1287","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","um 1200":"noin 1200","1240":"1240","1170":"1170","post 1214":"1214","Chiaravalle, Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italia":"Chiaravalle, Milano, Milano, Lombardia, Italia","Italy":"Italia"},"fr":{"um 1200–24 SEP 1265":"environ 1200–24 septembre 1265","1200–1265":"1200–1265","–1263":"–1263","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1220–Female":"1220–Décédée","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1170–1214":"1170–1214","24 SEP 1265":"24 septembre 1265","1214":"1214","um 1240":"environ 1240","1200":"1200","1287":"1287","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","um 1200":"environ 1200","1240":"1240","1170":"1170","post 1214":"1214","Chiaravalle, Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italia":"Chiaravalle, Milano, Milano, Lombardia, Italie","Italy":"Italie","lifeSummary":"Filippo della Torre est né environ 1200, fils de Giacomo II della Torre et Mattea della Torre. Il a épousé da Niguarda. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Sa profession de son indiquée est iv signore di milano e capitano perpetuo del popolo à Milano, Lombardia, Italie. Il est décédé le 24 septembre 1265, à l’âge de 66 ans, et a été enterré à Chiaravalle, Milano, Milano, Lombardia, Italie."},"de":{"um 1200–24 SEP 1265":"um 1200–24. September 1265","1200–1265":"1200–1265","–1263":"–1263","–Male":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1220–Female":"1220–Verstorben","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1170–1214":"1170–1214","24 SEP 1265":"24. September 1265","1214":"1214","um 1240":"um 1240","1200":"1200","1287":"1287","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","um 1200":"um 1200","1240":"1240","1170":"1170","post 1214":"1214","Chiaravalle, Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italia":"Chiaravalle, Milano, Milano, Lombardei, Italien","Italy":"Italien","lifeSummary":"Filippo della Torre wurde um 1200, als Sohn von Giacomo II della Torre und Mattea della Torre geboren. Er hat da Niguarda geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. sein Beruf ist als iv signore di milano e capitano perpetuo del popolo in Milano, Lombardei, Italien aufgeführt. Er starb am 24. September 1265 im Alter von 66 Jahren und wurde in Chiaravalle, Milano, Milano, Lombardei, Italien begraben."},"ht":{"um 1200–24 SEP 1265":"about 1200–24 September 1265","1200–1265":"1200–1265","–1263":"–1263